{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Review input is scoped to changed lines only, not full modified files.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module handoff: diff extraction -> review-input builder. MOCK-MISS: this is not just one pure function if scoping is lost between modules. REAL-INFRA no: behavior text is about payload scope, not OS/network semantics. LLM-DEP no: quote proving plumbing-only scope: \"review input is scoped to the lines that changed\"; quote excluding model-quality dependence: nothing about correctness of model judgment, only what input slice is sent. Rejected higher levels: System/Agentic are disqualified because behavior does not require real HTTP or model output content.","test_description":"Wire diff parser + prompt/input-construction modules with a synthetic PR diff containing large unchanged regions; assert the constructed review input includes only changed hunks and excludes unchanged file content.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.67,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments attach to correct diff positions on the PR.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA yes: correctness depends on real GitHub diff-position semantics and API behavior (line/path/side/commit mapping). MOCK-HIDE: mocked API can accept invalid mappings that real API rejects or renders incorrectly. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: no model-quality decision in behavior text, only placement mechanics.","test_description":"Against a real test PR, post inline comments using computed positions for added/modified/deleted lines, then fetch PR review comments from GitHub and verify each appears at intended path/line/side in diff view.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.8,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"descriptio