sion bug is detectable without real network. LLM-DEP no: quote proving plumbing-only scope: \"No inline finding is dropped\"; quote excluding model-content dependence: scope is completeness of transfer \"before posting,\" not whether findings are good. Rejected System/Agentic for lack of required real infra or model judgment.","test_description":"Feed multiple inline findings (including edge cases like duplicate-like text, long messages) through aggregation and summary construction modules; assert summary contains a one-to-one representation of all inline findings expected for posting.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Sequence read diff -> post inline comments -> post summary succeeds for a real PR using fixed precomputed findings.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA yes by behavior text: \"real pull request\" and real posting operations require actual HTTP/API sequencing and auth/rate-limit/error semantics. LLM-DEP no: quote proving deterministic plumbing-only scope: \"fixed precomputed finding set\"; quote excluding model-output dependence: findings are precomputed, so no model judgment is under test. Rejected Agentic/Workflow on that explicit exclusion.","test_description":"Run end-to-end against a real test PR with a static finding fixture: fetch diff from GitHub, post inline comments, then post summary; assert all API calls succeed and resulting artifacts are present and linked.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.84,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"Full live run with model-generated findings completes correctly for a real PR without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Both real infra and real model are involved, but minimum boundary must include model non-